[src:scim-provisioning-deep/lightweight-directory-access-protocol] The StartTLS operation establishes Transport Layer Security (the descendant of SSL) on the connection.
[src:scim-provisioning-deep/lightweight-directory-access-protocol] It can provide data confidentiality (to protect data from being observed by third parties) and/or data integrity protection (which protects the data from tampering).
[src:scim-provisioning-deep/lightweight-directory-access-protocol] During TLS negotiation the server sends its X.509 certificate to prove its identity.
